<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF93FF80FF7EFE87FBD8FE8C" box="[136,1071,338,364]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF7EFE87FBD8FE8C" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" box="[136,1071,338,364]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF7EFE87FEE4FE8C" bold="true" box="[136,275,338,364]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Named because of its occurrence only on French Polynesian islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF93FF80FF4BFEA0FDFAFE38" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFEA0FDFAFE38" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFEA0FECDFE6F" bold="true" box="[189,314,373,399]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—This species can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FC99FEA3FBB7FE70" box="[879,1088,374,400]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FC99FEA3FC1FFE70" box="[879,1000,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of stem and leaf scales, 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF93FF80FF2FFE4FFF19FE54" box="[217,238,410,436]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF93FF80FED0FE4FFECCFE54" box="[294,315,410,436]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
flowers together in some axils, filament length, yellow pollen, and the lack of bracts, combined with the size and colour of mature fruit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF93FF80FF4BFE34FC80FCA0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="description">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFE34FCADFD50" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFE34FEA6FE1B" bold="true" box="[189,337,481,507]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Description:</emphasis>
—Stem and leaf scales present. Leaf bases connate. Linear leaves unknown; expanded floating or submerged leaves unknown, leaves of terrestrial plants expanded 2.0– 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FC42FDD3FBFAFDC0" box="[948,1037,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FB98FDD3FB0EFDC0" box="[1134,1273,518,544]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.8 mm</quantity>
wide, venation simple, petiole 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FECDFDFFFE31FDA4" box="[315,454,554,580]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="1.95" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="1.2">1.2–2.7 mm</quantity>
long; 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF93FF80FDE2FDFFFDDEFDA4" box="[532,553,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF93FF80FD90FDFFFD8CFDA4" box="[614,635,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
flowers together in an axil opposed by a 
<specimenCount id="C9DCA4FFFF93FF80FB9CFDFFFB88FDA4" box="[1130,1151,554,580]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
flower. Bracts apparently lacking. Styles erect, caducous ≤1.0 mm long. Filament erect, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FCB6FD9BFC61FD88" box="[832,918,590,616]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long; anthers quadrilocular, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FB20FD9BFAAAFD88" box="[1238,1373,590,616]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FF7EFDA7FEF8FD6C" box="[136,271,626,652]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 mm</quantity>
wide; pollen yellow. Fruit substrumose, subsessile, slightly wider than high, uniform golden-brown when mature, 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FF12FD43FE9CFD50" box="[228,363,662,688]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FE37FD43FDC4FD50" box="[449,563,662,688]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1 mm</quantity>
wide, winged throughout.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFD6CFE2DFD34" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" box="[189,474,697,724]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFD6CFEAEFD33" bold="true" box="[189,345,697,723]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Illustrations:</emphasis>
— 
<figureCitation id="47E173F3FF93FF80FE81FD6FFE21FD34" box="[375,470,698,724]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1913,1935]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-15@17.[151,1436,190,1889]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Fruits of Callitriche in Oceania and Australasia: a—C. heterophylla, b—C. insularis, c—C. muelleri, d—C. palustris, e—C. papuana, f—C. peploides, g—C. petriei, h—C. platycarpa, i—C. sonderi, j—C. stagnalis, k—C. umbonata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577553/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Fig. 10b</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFD08FC80FCA0" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFD08FEA1FD17" bold="true" box="[189,342,733,759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FE84FD0BFE00FD18" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[370,503,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FE84FD0BFE00FD18" box="[370,503,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">C. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FC6BFD0BFB86FD18" box="[925,1137,734,760]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FC6BFD0BFBE1FD18" box="[925,1046,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region by the small, broadly winged fruit which are golden-brown when mature. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FBF3FCD7FB75FCFC" authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1856" box="[1029,1154,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muelleri">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FBF3FCD7FB75FCFC" box="[1029,1154,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">C. muelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but that species has leaves with a single tooth on each margin which is lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FD1BFCF3FC87FCA0" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[749,880,806,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FD1BFCF3FC87FCA0" box="[749,880,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">C. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF93FF80FF4BFC9CFE93FB64" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFC9CFAE5FC84" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" box="[189,1298,841,868]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFC9CFEAEFC83" bold="true" box="[189,345,841,867]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Native. Known only from Rapa Island and its satellite Tauturau, 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF93FF80FBBFFC9FFAF8FC84" box="[1097,1295,842,868]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFCB8FDDFFC30" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFCB8FE3CFC68" bold="true" box="[189,459,877,904]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
—Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FD7EFCBBFC9BFC68" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[648,876,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FD7EFCBBFC9BFC68" box="[648,876,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Callitriche insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been collected from a stream draining a taro patch, from a moss-covered seepage from a basalt outcrop above the sea and from the margin of a stream flowing through marshes. 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FEA6FC63FE44FC30" box="[336,435,950,976]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.505" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.01" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="m" value="150.5" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="1.0">1–300 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF93FF80FF4BFC0CFC8EFBDC" blockId="18.[136,1452,338,1156]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FF4BFC0CFE4AFC13" bold="true" box="[189,445,985,1011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF93FF80FE2FFC0FFD37FC14" authorityName="Lansdown" authorityYear="2022" box="[473,704,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF93FF80FE2FFC0FFD37FC14" box="[473,704,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">Callitriche insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only a very small number of specimens and is estimated to have an AOO significantly less than 
<quantity id="1822C293FF93FF80FD40FC2BFD09FBF8" box="[694,766,1022,1048]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="261" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
<superScript id="28AFC23EFF93FF80FD0BFC2BFCF2FBEC" attach="left" box="[765,773,1022,1036]" fontSize="6" pageId="18" pageNumber="261">2</superScript>
, such that it is very vulnerable to factors such as local landuse changes. It is therefore classed as Vulnerable D2 (
